                        <par_12
                            jcr:primaryType="nt:unstructured"
                            sling:resourceType="wcm/foundation/components/parsys">
                            <container4
                                cq:styleIds="[1653545847150,1653242825678,1653545825687,1653545835982]"
                                jcr:primaryType="nt:unstructured"
                                sling:resourceType="abbvie-com2/components/container/v2/container">
                                <title2
                                    cq:styleIds="[1659545825678,1651545824678,1651545829678,1651545825692]"
                                    jcr:lastModified="{Date}2024-05-08T09:36:17.589-04:00"
                                    jcr:lastModifiedBy="VALENSX5"
                                    jcr:primaryType="nt:unstructured"
                                    jcr:title="More than a headache"
                                    sling:resourceType="abbvie-com2/components/title/v2/title"
                                    type="h2"
                                    variant="h"/>
                                <text2
                                    cq:styleIds="[1659545825678,1659545835858]"
                                    jcr:lastModified="{Date}2023-04-06T11:50:44.958-04:00"
                                    jcr:lastModifiedBy="chiucx"
                                    jcr:primaryType="nt:unstructured"
                                    sling:resourceType="abbvie-com2/components/text/v2/text"
                                    text="&lt;p>Anna Maria Kollia still recalls the worst migraine she ever experienced at work. &lt;br>&#xd;&#xa;“I had to excuse myself from a meeting,” says Kollia, who lives in Athens, Greece, and works as eye care therapy lead for AbbVie’s Europe region. “I had to leave the office because it was extremely difficult for me to attend and concentrate during the meeting. I even took a taxi home because I wasn't able to drive.” &lt;br>&#xd;&#xa; &lt;br>&#xd;&#xa;Migraine is the second-most disabling condition in the world after low back pain and is the leading cause of missed work for people under age 50.&lt;sup>1,2&lt;/sup>&amp;nbsp;This missed work can be physically, mentally and financially taxing for workers and their employers. In a recent study of European patients living with migraine, nearly half of all respondents reported struggles fully functioning at work due to migraine.&lt;sup>3 &lt;/sup>&lt;br>&#xd;&#xa;&lt;br>&#xd;&#xa;Unfortunately, Kollia’s experience is a common one for people living with migraine in the workforce. Furthermore, colleagues often misunderstand what they are going through. 52 percent of people living with migraine wish their colleagues were more supportive during their migraine attacks, according to a recent AbbVie-sponsored survey in the U.S.&lt;sup>4&lt;/sup>&amp;nbsp;“It’s just a headache,” is a common misconception. &lt;/p>&#xd;&#xa;"
                                    textIsRich="true"/>
                            </container4>
                            <image
                                jcr:created="{Date}2023-01-06T18:11:16.941-05:00"
                                jcr:createdBy="chiucx"
                                jcr:lastModified="{Date}2023-01-06T18:11:23.937-05:00"
                                jcr:lastModifiedBy="chiucx"
                                jcr:primaryType="nt:unstructured"
                                sling:resourceType="abbvie-com2/components/image/v2/image"
                                altValueFromDAM="true"
                                displayPopupTitle="true"
                                fileReference="/content/dam/abbvie-com2/images/stories/making-it-migraine-friendly-why-were-reimagining-workplace/migraine-at-work-in-story-stat.jpg"
                                isDecorative="false"
                                titleValueFromDAM="true"/>
                            <container4_copy
                                cq:styleIds="[1653545847150,1653242825678,1653545825687,1653545835982]"
                                jcr:primaryType="nt:unstructured"
                                sling:resourceType="abbvie-com2/components/container/v2/container">
                                <separator
                                    cq:styleIds="[1662756456518]"
                                    jcr:created="{Date}2023-01-06T18:14:03.003-05:00"
                                    jcr:createdBy="chiucx"
                                    jcr:lastModified="{Date}2023-01-06T18:14:03.003-05:00"
                                    jcr:lastModifiedBy="chiucx"
                                    jcr:primaryType="nt:unstructured"
                                    sling:resourceType="abbvie-com2/components/separator/v2/separator"/>
                                <text2
                                    cq:styleIds="[1659545825678,1659545835858]"
                                    jcr:lastModified="{Date}2023-01-06T18:14:16.862-05:00"
                                    jcr:lastModifiedBy="chiucx"
                                    jcr:primaryType="nt:unstructured"
                                    sling:resourceType="abbvie-com2/components/text/v2/text"
                                    text="&lt;p>To support employees living with migraine, companies are beginning to invest in migraine-friendly workspaces. AbbVie is going even further. As part of the company’s commitment to the migraine community and advancing research across the spectrum of migraine, AbbVie has launched training and resources to support employees who live with migraine&lt;br>&#xd;&#xa;&lt;br>&#xd;&#xa;“We’re driven by the health and emotional well-being of our employees,” says Lesli Marasco, head of global benefits, AbbVie. “We strive every day to achieve an inclusive work environment and culture promoting the health and well-being of our people and offering an environment where our employees can be their best selves at work and at home.”&lt;/p>&#xd;&#xa;"
                                    textIsRich="true"/>
                                <separator_copy
                                    cq:styleIds="[1662756456518]"
                                    jcr:created="{Date}2023-01-06T18:14:03.003-05:00"
                                    jcr:createdBy="chiucx"
                                    jcr:lastModified="{Date}2023-01-06T18:14:03.003-05:00"
                                    jcr:lastModifiedBy="chiucx"
                                    jcr:primaryType="nt:unstructured"
                                    sling:resourceType="abbvie-com2/components/separator/v2/separator"/>
                                <title
                                    cq:styleIds="[1659545825678,1651545825694]"
                                    jcr:created="{Date}2023-01-06T18:14:29.531-05:00"
                                    jcr:createdBy="chiucx"
                                    jcr:lastModified="{Date}2024-05-08T09:36:34.455-04:00"
                                    jcr:lastModifiedBy="VALENSX5"
                                    jcr:primaryType="nt:unstructured"
                                    jcr:title="Inside the migraine-friendly workplace "
                                    sling:resourceType="abbvie-com2/components/title/v2/title"
                                    type="h3"
                                    variant="h"/>
                                <text2_copy
                                    cq:styleIds="[1659545825678,1659545835858]"
                                    jcr:lastModified="{Date}2023-01-06T18:15:42.443-05:00"
                                    jcr:lastModifiedBy="chiucx"
                                    jcr:primaryType="nt:unstructured"
                                    sling:resourceType="abbvie-com2/components/text/v2/text"
                                    text="&lt;p>Migraine-friendly workplaces are customized to reduce things that might either trigger a migraine or make it hard to work while managing one. Natural lighting, calm noise levels and quiet rooms, filtered air to remove odors and opportunities to stay hydrated are all key ingredients. &lt;br>&#xd;&#xa;&lt;br>&#xd;&#xa;“As an innovation-driven company, we at AbbVie value diverse perspectives and are committed to making key adaptations to mitigate the workplace risk factors and create an inclusive culture where all employees feel supported and respected,” says Pilar Marquez, head of human resources, Europe area, AbbVie.  &lt;/p>&#xd;&#xa;"
                                    textIsRich="true"/>
                            </container4_copy>
                            <quote
                                cq:styleIds="[1000000000000,1000000000040]"
                                jcr:created="{Date}2023-01-06T18:15:51.170-05:00"
                                jcr:createdBy="chiucx"
                                jcr:lastModified="{Date}2023-01-06T18:16:06.168-05:00"
                                jcr:lastModifiedBy="chiucx"
                                jcr:primaryType="nt:unstructured"
                                sling:resourceType="abbvie-com2/components/quote"
                                attributionName="Pilar Marquez"
                                attributionTitle="head of human resources, Europe area, AbbVie"
                                quote="When everyone can be themselves at work and when they’re treated with respect and dignity, we maximize every employee’s potential."
                                quoteType="regular"
                                textSize="h0"/>
                            <container4_copy_copy
                                cq:styleIds="[1653545847150,1653242825678,1653545825687,1653545835982]"
                                jcr:primaryType="nt:unstructured"
                                sling:resourceType="abbvie-com2/components/container/v2/container">
                                <separator
                                    cq:styleIds="[1662756456518]"
                                    jcr:created="{Date}2023-01-06T18:14:03.003-05:00"
                                    jcr:createdBy="chiucx"
                                    jcr:lastModified="{Date}2023-01-06T18:14:03.003-05:00"
                                    jcr:lastModifiedBy="chiucx"
                                    jcr:primaryType="nt:unstructured"
                                    sling:resourceType="abbvie-com2/components/separator/v2/separator"/>
                                <title_copy
                                    cq:styleIds="[1659545825678,1651545825694]"
                                    jcr:created="{Date}2023-01-06T18:14:29.531-05:00"
                                    jcr:createdBy="chiucx"
                                    jcr:lastModified="{Date}2024-05-08T09:36:28.462-04:00"
                                    jcr:lastModifiedBy="VALENSX5"
                                    jcr:primaryType="nt:unstructured"
                                    jcr:title="Creating a more migraine-friendly environment"
                                    sling:resourceType="abbvie-com2/components/title/v2/title"
                                    type="h3"
                                    variant="h"/>
                                <text2
                                    cq:styleIds="[1659545825678,1659545835858]"
                                    jcr:lastModified="{Date}2023-01-06T18:25:37.795-05:00"
                                    jcr:lastModifiedBy="chiucx"
                                    jcr:primaryType="nt:unstructured"
                                    sling:resourceType="abbvie-com2/components/text/v2/text"
                                    text="&lt;p>Having lived with migraine for more than a decade, Kollia has become keenly aware of the ways that her work environment influences her workday. &lt;br>&#xd;&#xa;&lt;br>&#xd;&#xa;She describes her office layout and work-life environment today as tools that can help prevent migraine triggers. Many of these design features and programs, from ergonomic equipment and silent workplace areas to easy access to water and natural light, were put in place by AbbVie to support people with migraine. These features were recognized by the European Migraine &amp;amp; Headache Association (EMHA), who awarded its&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.emhalliance.org/for-workplaces/&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;>Migraine Friendly Workplace Stamp&lt;/a>&amp;nbsp;to AbbVie in summer 2022.  &lt;br>&#xd;&#xa;&lt;br>&#xd;&#xa;“These initiatives help us to measure our progress in this area, to retain and attract new employees who want to work in a friendly and inclusive environment,” says Marquez. &lt;/p>&#xd;&#xa;"
                                    textIsRich="true"/>
                                <separator_copy
                                    cq:styleIds="[1662756456518]"
                                    jcr:created="{Date}2023-01-06T18:14:03.003-05:00"
                                    jcr:createdBy="chiucx"
                                    jcr:lastModified="{Date}2023-01-06T18:14:03.003-05:00"
                                    jcr:lastModifiedBy="chiucx"
                                    jcr:primaryType="nt:unstructured"
                                    sling:resourceType="abbvie-com2/components/separator/v2/separator"/>
                                <title
                                    cq:styleIds="[1659545825678,1651545825694]"
                                    jcr:created="{Date}2023-01-06T18:14:29.531-05:00"
                                    jcr:createdBy="chiucx"
                                    jcr:lastModified="{Date}2024-05-08T09:36:45.453-04:00"
                                    jcr:lastModifiedBy="VALENSX5"
                                    jcr:primaryType="nt:unstructured"
                                    jcr:title="A data-driven approach to fighting migraine at work "
                                    sling:resourceType="abbvie-com2/components/title/v2/title"
                                    type="h3"
                                    variant="h"/>
                                <text2_copy
                                    cq:styleIds="[1659545825678,1659545835858]"
                                    jcr:lastModified="{Date}2023-01-06T18:26:00.665-05:00"
                                    jcr:lastModifiedBy="chiucx"
                                    jcr:primaryType="nt:unstructured"
                                    sling:resourceType="abbvie-com2/components/text/v2/text"
                                    text="&lt;p>In the U.S., AbbVie’s Health Economics and Outcomes Research (HEOR) team is conducting real-world evidence research among its own employees to help inform its migraine-workplace strategy and develop an evidence-based scalable employer program for migraine education. The research underway will help answer foundational questions about the employee experience to create a model of what migraine management leadership can look like.   &lt;br>&#xd;&#xa;&lt;br>&#xd;&#xa;The study was created with the goal of understanding 1) the burden associated with migraine and how individuals manage migraine within AbbVie’s employee population and 2) the impact of workplace educational programs on these outcomes. By uncovering the burden of the disease and potentially demonstrating the impact of a workplace educational program on reducing the burden, AbbVie can empower our employees to manage their disease better and help others to do so. &lt;/p>&#xd;&#xa;"
                                    textIsRich="true"/>
                            </container4_copy_copy>
                            <quote_copy
                                cq:styleIds="[1000000000000,1000000000040]"
                                jcr:created="{Date}2023-01-06T18:15:51.170-05:00"
                                jcr:createdBy="chiucx"
                                jcr:lastModified="{Date}2023-01-06T18:27:30.037-05:00"
                                jcr:lastModifiedBy="chiucx"
                                jcr:primaryType="nt:unstructured"
                                sling:resourceType="abbvie-com2/components/quote"
                                attributionName="Darshini Shah"
                                attributionTitle="director, global health economics and outcomes research strategy, AbbVie"
                                quote="We often look at the direct health care costs of migraine, but there's also an indirect cost through lost productivity, which is a significant part of migraine burden because migraine often starts during someone’s prime working years."
                                quoteType="regular"
                                textSize="h0"/>
                            <container4_copy_1766019692
                                cq:styleIds="[1653545847150,1653242825678,1653545825687,1653545835982]"
                                jcr:primaryType="nt:unstructured"
                                sling:resourceType="abbvie-com2/components/container/v2/container">
                                <text2
                                    cq:styleIds="[1659545825678,1659545835858]"
                                    jcr:lastModified="{Date}2023-01-06T18:27:45.513-05:00"
                                    jcr:lastModifiedBy="chiucx"
                                    jcr:primaryType="nt:unstructured"
                                    sling:resourceType="abbvie-com2/components/text/v2/text"
                                    text="&lt;p>“Our hope is that the study shines a light on this under-recognized disease, illuminates the unmet need and shares what we’ve learned so that employers better understand the value of a migraine-friendly workplace,” says Shah, who helped design the study.&lt;br>&#xd;&#xa;&lt;br>&#xd;&#xa;The study is part of a larger workplace initiative underway with the Migraine at Work organization, a World Health Education effort. While the study is still ongoing, AbbVie has resources and virtual trainings for its U.S. employees to support overall well-being, many of which are also helpful to reduce the impact of migraine — including meditation, diet, stress management and fitness activities — in the workplace.  &lt;br>&#xd;&#xa;&lt;br>&#xd;&#xa;According to Kollia, the support she now receives from AbbVie and her colleagues is a game changer. &lt;br>&#xd;&#xa;&lt;br>&#xd;&#xa;“I have worked with colleagues that both have and have not understood the impact of migraine at work,” she says. “Just having people understand and support you is a game changer. That understanding and support makes a big difference for me every day at work.”&lt;/p>&#xd;&#xa;"
                                    textIsRich="true"/>
                                <accordion
                                    cq:styleIds="[1]"
                                    jcr:created="{Date}2023-01-06T18:28:11.582-05:00"
                                    jcr:createdBy="chiucx"
                                    jcr:lastModified="{Date}2023-01-06T18:28:34.667-05:00"
                                    jcr:lastModifiedBy="chiucx"
                                    jcr:primaryType="nt:unstructured"
                                    sling:resourceType="abbvie-com2/components/accordion/v2/accordion"
                                    headingElement="h5"
                                    singleExpansion="false">
                                    <item_1673047709950
                                        cq:panelTitle="References"
                                        cq:styleIds="[1659545825678]"
                                        jcr:lastModified="{Date}2023-01-06T18:30:29.681-05:00"
                                        jcr:lastModifiedBy="chiucx"
                                        jcr:primaryType="nt:unstructured"
                                        sling:resourceType="abbvie-com2/components/text/v2/text"
                                        text="&lt;p>1 Steiner, T.J., Stovner, L.J., Jensen, R. et al.&lt;br />&#xd;&#xa;Migraine remains second among the world’s causes of disability, and first among young women: findings from GBD2019. J Headache Pain 21, 137 (2020).&lt;br />&#xd;&#xa;&lt;a href=&quot;https://doi.org/10.1186/s10194-020-01208-0&quot;>https://doi.org&lt;/a>&lt;br />&#xd;&#xa;&lt;a href=&quot;https://thejournalofheadacheandpain.biomedcentral.com/articles/10.1186/s10194-020-01208-0/tables/2&quot;>https://thejournalofheadacheandpain.biomedcentral.com/&lt;/a>&lt;/p>&#xd;&#xa;&lt;p>2 Shimizu T, Sakai F, Miyake H, Sone T, Sato M, Tanabe S, Azuma Y, Dodick DW. Disability, quality of life, productivity impairment and employer costs of migraine in the workplace.&lt;br />&#xd;&#xa;J Headache Pain. 2021 Apr 21;22(1):29.&lt;br />&#xd;&#xa;doi: 10.1186/s10194-021-01243-5.&lt;br />&#xd;&#xa;PMID: 33882816; PMCID: PMC8061063. &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC8061063/#:~:text=Migraine%20is%20the%20leading%20cause,productivity%20losses%20in%20the%20workplace&quot;>https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov&lt;/a>&lt;/p>&#xd;&#xa;&lt;p>3 Ruiz de la Torre, E. R., Vicente-Herrero, T., Ramírez-Iñiguez de la Torre, V., &amp;amp; Capdevila-García, L. (2019). Migraine at work:&lt;br />&#xd;&#xa;European survey. Analysis of results and conclusions. European Migraine and Headache Alliance, 341.&lt;br />&#xd;&#xa;Available at: &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.emhalliance.org/wp-content/uploads/EMHA-Migraine-at-work.pdf&quot;>https://www.emhalliance.org&lt;/a>.&lt;br />&#xd;&#xa;Accessed on May 10, 2021.&lt;/p>&#xd;&#xa;&lt;p>4 Working Through Migraine Survey 2022, conducted online in the US by The Harris Poll, sponsored by AbbVie. &lt;/p>&#xd;&#xa;"
                                        textIsRich="true"/>
                                </accordion>
